DOCUMENT();        # This should be the first executable line in the problem.

loadMacros(
"PG.pl",
"PGbasicmacros.pl",
"PGchoicemacros.pl",
"PGanswermacros.pl",
"PGauxiliaryFunctions.pl"
);

TEXT(beginproblem());
$showPartialCorrectAnswers = 1;

$a1 = random(2,9,1);
$b1 = random(2,9,1);
$c1 = sqrt($b1/$a1);
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
Consider the function \( f(x) = $a1 x + $b1 x ^ { -1 } \).
For this function there are four important intervals:
 \( (-\infty, A] \), \( [A,B) \),\( (B,C) \), and \( [C,\infty) \) where
 \( A \), and \( C \) are the critical numbers and the
 function is not defined at \( B \).
$BR
Find \( A \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = -$c1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( B \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = 0;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
and  \( C \) \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = $c1;
ANS(num_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
For each of the following intervals, tell whether \( f(x) \)
is increasing (type in INC) or decreasing (type in DEC).
$BR
 \( (-\infty, A] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "INC";
ANS(num_cmp($ans, strings=>['INC','DEC']));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [A,B) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "DEC";
ANS(num_cmp($ans, strings=>['INC','DEC']));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( (B,C] \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "DEC";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
TEXT(EV2(<<EOT));
$BR
\( [C,\infty) \): \{ans_rule(10) \}
EOT
$ans = "INC";
ANS(str_cmp($ans));
ENDDOCUMENT();        # This should be the last executable line in the problem.
